    What is the most expensive Mir painting?
    PEINTURE
    The artist's highest auction price since 1998 is 37,064,980 USD for PEINTURE (TOILE BLEUE), which was sold at Sotheby's London in 2012.20 Nov 2023

    What is Joan Mir's most famous art piece?
    The Farm
    The Farm (19201922) is a vivid representation of Mir's Catalan heritage and one of his most famous works. This painting blends the precision of Cubism with a deep sense of personal symbolism.10 Jan 2025

    How many paintings did Joan Mir do?
    Mir was incredibly prolific. He produced approximately 2,000 paintings, 500 sculptures, 400 ceramics, 5,000 drawings, and 1,000 lithographs.15 Jun 2015

    About

    Description

    Joan Mir i Ferr was a Catalan Spanish painter, sculptor and ceramist. A museum dedicated to his work, the Fundaci Joan Mir, was established in his native city of Barcelona in 1975, and another, the Fundaci Pilar i Joan Mir, was established in his adoptive city of Palma in 1981. Wikipedia
    Born: April 20, 1893, Barcelona
    Died: December 25, 1983 (age 90 years), Palma
    Periods: Surrealism, Modern art, Dada
    Influenced by: Pablo Picasso, Andr Breton, Hans Arp, Andr Masson, Hieronymus Bosch, Tristan Tzara, Modest Urgell
    Children: Mara Dolores Mir
    Education: Cercle Artstic de Sant Lluc
